    All Classes and Interfaces

    Class
    Description
    Applicant
     
    ApplicantController
     
    Application
    Represents base class for all types of applications submitted by users, like BTO applications or officer registration requests.
    ApplicationController
    Handles operations related to user applications within the system, like submitting new applications, processing approvals or rejections, and retrieving application records by ID
    ApplicationRepository
     
    ApplicationStatus
    Enum representing the statuses an application can have - BOOKED, APPROVED, PENDING, REJECTED Each status is associated with an integer value
    AuthController
    Handles the authentication process during login.
    BTOApplication
    Represents a BTO application submitted by an applicant for a specific project and unit type This class extends the general Application class and includes additional details specific to BTO applications, like the associated project, applicant, and unit type.
    BTOApplicationController
    Controller for managing BTO applications.
    BTOApplicationView
    A menu view that displays all applicable projects for the user to apply.
    ChangePasswordForm
    A form view that handles the process of changing a user's password.
    Config
     
    CreateProjectListingForm
    A form view that handles the process of creating a new project listing.
    CreateUnitTypeForm
    A form view that handles the process of creating a new unit type for a project.
    DateHelper
     
    DefaultHomeView
    A menu view that displays the default home view for the user.
    EditListingForm
    A form view that handles the process of editing an existing project listing.
    EditUnitForm
    A form view that handles the process of editing an existing unit type.
    EnquiriesView
    This class is responsible for managing all enquiries in the system.
    Enquiry
    Represents an individual enquiry message in the system.
    EnquiryController
    Controller class responsible for managing Enquiries between users.
    HDBManager
    Represents a HDB Manager who manages all housing projects.
    HDBManagerHomeView
    This class represents the home view for HDB Manager.
    HDBOfficer
    Represents a HDB Officer who oversees specific housing projects.
    HDBOfficerController
    Controller class to manage HDB Officer operations Allows officer to register for a project, checking registration status, updating flat availability, updating applicant bookings, and generating booking receipts
    HDBOfficerHomeView
     
    HomeViewFactory
     
    IFormView
     
    IMenuView
     
    InputValidator
    Utility class for validating user inputs across the application.
    IView
     
    LoginForm
    A form view that handles the process of logging in a user.
    MainApp
     
    ManageApplicationView
    This class represents the view for managing all BTO Project and Officer applications.
    ManageOfficerApplicationView
     
    ManageProjectApplicationView
    This view class is responsible for managing all BTO project applications.
    ManagerProjectManagementView
    Represents the view for HDB Managers to manage BTO projects.
    MyProfileView
    A menu view that displays the user's profile options.
    OfficerProjectManagementView
     
    Project
    Represents the Build To Order housing project.
    ProjectController
    Handles operations related to BTO project and managaing units like creating, editing, deleting projects and unit types, and filtering based on eligibility.
    ProjectDetailView
    A menu view that displays the details of a specific project.
    ProjectListingView
    A menu view that displays all applicable projects for the user.
    ProjectOfficerApplication
    Represents an application made by a project officer.
    ProjectOfficerApplicationController
    Responsible for managing Project Officer applications.
    ProjectRepository
     
    RegistrationController
    Controller responsible for handling the registration of new users.
    RegistrationForm
    A form view that handles the process of registering a new user.
    Session
    Singleton class that represents the current session in the system.
    StartUpView
    A menu view that displays the startup options for the user.
    UnitType
    Represents a specific type of housing unit in a BTO project.
    User
    Represents a user in the system with attributes such as UId, name, age, and marital status.
    UserController
    This class provides functionalities to manage operations such as changing passwords and logging out.
    UserFactory
    A factory class that creates a typed user based on given role.
    UserRepository
     
    UserRole
    Enum representing different user roles in the system.
